7/7 in an online setting, but I'm going to be forever grateful that I have. Be good to each other ü§ù Love you Winky üíò

6/7 The absolutely hilarious Twitter spaces this morning with Cloot @CloutedMind Wanky @0xwinky Mooshy @itmemushy Lobsy @Lobes604 and the baked cousin greg @doctoryuca had me cracking up to the point of literal tears. I never imagined making this many friends ...

5/7 The fact that somebody I only met a few months ago would be so friendly, generous, and caring, is something that moves me nearly to tears. The whole ngmi vibe I felt this morning has completely dissipated, and I've been reinvigorated with the wgmi spirit (was that cringey?)

4/7 While at a pretty low point I reached out to my friend @0xwinky and let him know my plan about taking time off. Not only does he give me a pep talk, but offers, no, insists on helping out with the additional cost to help me get this beautiful @CoolmanUniverse (hi speshies!) https://t.co/58OtTwhUpp

3/7 I'm so thrilled to see my friends making it, I know how life-changing it can be and it couldn't be happening to better groups of people. But when you're an outsider looking in, it kind of stings, you know?

2/7 After waking up and coming to terms with losing out on god knows how many whitelists over the last few weeks, I was at my wits' end and ready to take a hiatus for a few days/weeks to clear my head. The grind has been tough, I'm not gonna lie.

gm

1/7 In this post I'd like to try to find the words to express my gratitude to a good friend of mine @0xwinky. I've tried to write this a few times, but each time I've found myself still unable to articulate exactly what his gestures mean to me.

After having sold my first to take some profit, I couldn't be more excited to rejoin the @CoolmanUniverse gang!
